        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 25 at 5:28PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Farmerville, or 16 miles southwest of Huttig, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lapile, Marion, Oakland, Cecil and Litroe.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
